0Conference%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20lower-income%20consumers%20%26quot%3Bare%20just%20choosing%20to%20eat%20at%20home%20more%20often.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20think%20of%20the%20informal%20eating-out%20sector%2C%20it's%20certainly%20likely%20this%20year%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20see%20negative%20traffic%20from%20a%20broad%20standpoint%2C%20from%20an%20industry%20standpoint%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorden%20said%20that%20this%20was%20partly%20because%20inflation%20is%20currently%20much%20higher%20for%20dining%20out%20than%20it%20is%20for%20buying%20groceries.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20meals%20at%20limited-service%20restaurants%20%E2%80%94%20those%20where%20you%20pay%20before%20ordering%20and%20typically%20don't%20get%20table%20service%20%E2%80%94%20went%20up%205.2%25%20in%20the%20year%20to%20February%2C%20compared%20to%20just%201%25%20for%20groceries%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fcpi.t02.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics'%20consumer%20price%20index.%20Some%20diners%20have%20complained%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-price-loses-lower-income-customers-inflation-pressure-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efast%20food%20is%20too%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorden%20also%20said%20lower-income%20consumers%20had%20burned%20through%20much%20of%20their%20savings%20from%20the%20pandemic.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20challenging%20consumer%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20fast-food%20chains%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-price-hikes-putting-off-low-income-customers-inflation-expensive-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%20increased%20menu%20prices%20significantly%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20pandemic%20amid%20soaring%20wage%20and%20commodity%20inflation.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20previously%20said%20that%20it%20raised%20US%20prices%20by%20around%2010%25%20in%20both%202022%20and%202023.%20Borden%20said%20this%20was%20a%20major%20contributor%20to%20McDonald's%20system-wide%20sales%20growing%20by%20more%20than%2030%25%20since%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%20that%20inflation%20is%20cooling%2C%20McDonald's%20won't%20be%20putting%20prices%20up%20as%20much%2C%20he%20said.%20He%20had%20told%20investors%20in%20February%20that%20consumers%20were%20%26quot%3Bwary%26quot%3B%20of%20price%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMcDonald's%20will%20focus%20on%20value%20bundles%20and%20app%20offers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22mcdonalds%20fries%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61b118e91655ab0018a6c06e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222304%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMcDonald's%20fries.%3Cp%3EErin%20McDowell%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELower-income%20consumers%20are%20expecting%20greater%20value%20for%20money%20than%20they%20did%20before%2C%20Borden%20said%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20consumers%20in%202024%20are%20going%20to%20be%20much%20more%20focused%20on%20affordability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20certainly%20what%20we're%20going%20to%20focus%20on%20and%20emphasize.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%20would%2C%20for%20example%2C%20promote%20its%20value%20deals%20more%20heavily%2C%20such%20as%20bundles%20in%20the%20US%20that%20come%20in%20at%20under%20%244%2C%20Borden%20said.%20In%20Germany%2C%20its%20McSmart%20offer%2C%20where%20customers%20can%20get%20two%20burgers%2C%20fries%2C%20and%20a%20drink%20for%205.99%20euros%20(around%20%246.55)%2C%20has%20performed%20%26quot%3Bincredibly%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorden%20added%20that%20McDonald's%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Blot%20more%20active%26quot%3B%20in%20using%20its%20app%20to%20give%20o