w-ecs-124031400467_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Belongs%2C%20and%20How%3F%20Locating%20the%20CAA%20in%20Today's%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F29170506%2Fimage4.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20from%20the%20introduction%20of%20Anupama%20Roy%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fem%3ECitizenship%20Regimes%2C%20Law%20and%20Belonging%3A%20The%20CAA%20and%20the%20NRC%3Cem%3E%2C%20Oxford%20University%20Press%2C%202022.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeventy%20years%20after%20the%20installation%20of%20republican%20citizenship%20through%20the%20termination%20of%20ties%20with%20the%20colonial%20regime%20and%20the%20inscription%20of%C2%A0%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EWe%20the%20People%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0as%20the%20%E2%80%98source%E2%80%99%20of%20authority%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20citizenship%20in%20India%20has%20become%20deeply%20contested.%20While%20there%20were%20contests%20over%20citizenship%20in%20the%20past%2C%20the%20contemporary%20period%20is%20distinctive%20for%20the%20unprecedented%20display%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98heightened%20consciousness%E2%80%99%20(Heater%201999%2C%20Faulks%202000)%20about%20citizenship%2C%20which%20spans%20the%20breadth%20of%20the%20country.%20This%20%E2%80%98citizenship%20consciousness%E2%80%99%20has%20become%20manifest%20in%20the%20deep%20fault-lines%20caused%20by%20changes%20in%20the%20citizenship%20law%2C%20which%20has%20produced%20a%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ecitizenship%20regime%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0inconsistent%20with%20the%20constitutional%20imaginary.%C2%A0%20In%20the%20summer%20of%202016%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20led%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20introduced%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Bill%20(CAB)%20in%20the%20Parliament%20which%20was%20entrusted%20to%20a%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20(JPC)%20for%20scrutiny.%20The%20CAB%20was%20eventually%20passed%20in%20December%202019%20when%20the%20NDA%20returned%20to%20power%20in%20May%202019%20with%20an%20overwhelming%20majority%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20In%20enacting%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%202019%2C%20the%20ruling%20NDA%20invoked%20the%20constitutionally%20mandated%20power%20of%20the%20Parliament%20to%20legislate%20on%20all%20matters%20pertaining%20to%20citizenship.%20The%20CAA%202019%20was%20brought%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20offering%20citizenship%20to%20those%20Hindus%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Christians%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Jains%20and%20Parsis%20who%20had%20fled%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20Afghanistan%20to%20escape%20religious%20persecution%20and%20had%20sought%20refuge%20in%20India%20before%2031%20December%202014.%20BJP%20leaders%20asserted%20that%20the%20amendment%20was%20essential%20to%20correct%20historical%20injustices%20caused%20by%20the%20partition%20of%20the%20country%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%20and%20the%20failure%20of%20Pakistan%20to%20protect%20its%20minorities%2C%20to%20which%20both%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20had%20committed%20themselves%20in%201950.%20Through%20this%20articulation%2C%20the%20CAA%202019%20recognised%20the%20right%20of%20specified%20religious%20communities%20to%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ereturn%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98home%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20the%20fulfilment%20of%20a%20moral%20claim%20to%20obtain%20the%20legal%20protection%20of%20citizenship%2C%20whose%20denial%20would%20perpetuate%20a%20historical%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20388px)%2085vw%2C%20388px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14154746%2F9780192859082-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22388%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14154746%2F9780192859082-1.jpg%20773w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14154746%2F9780192859082-1-193x300.jpg%20193w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14154746%2F9780192859082-1-660x1024.jpg%20660w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-701624%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22602%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAnupama%20Roy%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3ECitizenship%20Regimes%2C%20Law%2C%20and%20Belonging%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EOxford%20University%20Press%2C%202022%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20work%20I%20would%20attempt%20to%20bring%20the%20CAA%20to%20an%20anthropological%20scrutiny%2C%20locating%20the%20contemporary%20form%20and%20content%20of%20the%20citizenship%20law%20in%20a%20%E2%80%98matrix%E2%80%A6%20of%20historical%20experience%E2%80%99%20(Guha%201982%2C%20140-141).%20The%20law%20of%20citizenship%20in%20India%20may%20be%20seen%20as%20located%20within%20a%20realm%20of%20contestation%20over%20ideas%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ewho%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0belongs%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ehow%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20history%20of%20this%20contest%20and%20its%20resolution%20show%20distinct%C2%A0%3Cem%3Elogics%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ethrough%20which%20membership%20and%20terms%20of%20belonging%20were%20laid%20down%20in%20law%2C%20entrenching%20successive%20citizenship%20regimes.%20The%20association%20of%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98regime%E2%80%99%20with%20citizenship%20is%20crucial%20for%20making%20the%20argument%20that%20law%20must%20be%20seen%20not%20only%20in%20terms%20of%20its%20bare%20provisions%2C%20but%20also%20examined%20for%20its%20political%20and%20ideological%20embeddedness.%20The%20%E2%80%98bare%20act%E2%80%99%20of%20citizenship%20which%20comes%20to%20us%20as%20an%20accumulation%20of%20successive%20amendments%20represents%20the%20law%E2%80%99s%20coalescent%20present.%20The%20different%20temporalities%20of%20law%20are%20compressed%20in%20the%20bare%20act%2C%20occluding%20the%20historical%20layers%20and%20flows%20that%20have%20marked%20the%20changes%20that%20occurred%20through%20successive%20amendments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECitizenship%20in%20contemporary%20India%20represents%20a%20coalescence%20of%20tendencies%20which%20have%20emanated%20from%20successive%20citizenship%20regimes%20spawned%20by%20the%20earlier%20periods%20of%20change%20in%20the%20citizenship%20law.%20The%20amendment%20in%202003%20may%20be%20considered%20a%20hinge%20point%20from%20which%20the%20NRC%20and%20the%20CAA%20emerged%20and%20have%20become%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20ideological%20landscape%20of%20citizenship%20in%20contemporary%20India.%20Having%20emerged%20as%20discrete%20tendencies%20out%20of%20the%202003%20amendment%20in%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%2C%20the%20NRC%20and%20CAA%20have%20become%20conjoined%20to%20produce%20a%20spectre%20of%20national%20citizenship%20based%20on%20the%20logic%20of%20descent%20as%20the%20organising%20principle.%20While%20the%20NRC%2C%20as%20the%20experience%20in%20Assam%20has%20shown%20us%2C%20is%20a%20legal%20regime%20of%20enumeration%20of%20Indian%20citizens%20based%20on%20evidence%20that%20establishes%20a%20legacy%20of%20inherited%20belonging%2C%20it%20is%20simultaneously%2C%20and%20often%20primarily%2C%20presented%20as%20a%20modality%20of%20identifying%20illegal%20migrants.%20The%20CAA%20is%20embedded%20in%20the%20idea%20of%20national-majoritarian%20citizenship%20with%20religion%20as%20its%20distinguishing%20principle.%20The%20CAA%20makes%20a%20distinction%20among%20illegal%20migrants%20to%20identify%20those%20among%20them%20who%20would%20be%20considered%20eligible%20for%20Indian%20citizenship%20through%20naturalisation.%20These%20two%20principles%20%E2%80%93%20of%20descent%20as%20the%20organising%20principle%20of%20citizenship%20and%20religion-based%20citizenship%20%E2%80%93%20have%20coalesced%20in%20the%20ruling%20practices%20of%20the%20current%20political%20regime%20to%20become%20decisive%20in%20determining%20who%20belongs%20to%20the%20political%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20inscription%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Assam%20exception%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%2C%20the%20IMDT%20Act%201983%20and%20its%20repeal%20in%202005%2C%20and%20the%20Assam%20Accord%20have%20reverberated%20in%20the%20contemporary%20landscape%20of%20citizenship.%20Indeed%2C%20the%20framing%20of%20illegality%20within%20which%20immigration%20from%20Bangladesh%20came%20to%20be%20seen%20in%20a%20national%20security%20framework%2C%20was%20reiterated%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgement%20in%20the%20Assam%20Samhilita%20Mahasangh%20case%20in%20December%202014%2C%20in%20which%20the%20court%20laid%20down%20the%20framework%20for%20updating%20the%20NRC%20in%20Assam.%20Indeed%2C%20in%20an%20extension%20of%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20position%20in%20the%20Sarbanand%20Sonowal%20Case%20(2005)%2C%20it%20made%20the%20fortification%20of%20territorial%20boundaries%20as%20well%20as%20the%20protection%20of%20population%20a%20function%20of%20state%20sovereignty.%20The%20persistence%20of%20the%20Sarbanand%20Sonowal%20judgement%20in%20contemporary%20debates%20on%20citizenship%20is%20seen%20in%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20the%20JPC%20in%20recommending%20the%20CAB%202016%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20Parliament%2C%20quoted%20the%20judgement%20to%20assert%20that%20%E2%80%98misconceived%E2%80%99%20ideas%20of%20secularism%20must%20not%20come%20in%20the%20way%20of%20extending%20the%20protection%20of%20citizenship%20to%20non-Muslim%20religious%20minorities%20who%20faced%20persecution%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20Bangladesh%20and%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%A6The%20CAA%20represents%20a%20tendency%20in%20the%20ideological%20formulation%20of%20citizenship%20that%20redefines%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20political%20community.%20If%20the%20NRC%20as%20it%20has%20unfolded%20in%20Assam%20congealed%20the%20relationship%20between%20legal%20status%20and%20blood%20ties%2C%20the%20CAA%20has%20installed%20an%20exclusionary%20nationhood%20under%20the%20veneer%20of%20liberal%20citizenship.%20The%20CAA%202019%20purports%20to%20extend%20the%20protection%20of%20citizenship%20to%20those%20facing%20religious%20persecution%20and%20simultaneously%20puts%20in%20place%20a%20regime%20which%20discriminates%20on%20the%20ground%20of%20religion.%20Amidst%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20nation-wide%20NRC%2C%20the%20CAA%20made%20the%20question%20of%20%E2%80%98documentary%20citizenship%E2%80%99%20(Sadiq%202009)%20more%20perplexing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnupama%20Roy%20is%20also%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.oup.com%2Fproduct%2Fcitizenship-in-india-9780199467969%3Fsearchbox_input%3Danupama%2520roy%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Findia.oup.com%2Fproduct%2Fcitizenship-in-india-9780199467969%3Fsearchbox_input%253Danupama%252520roy%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710497833654000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2f2Us7UtIWEULdJ5yrHgBj%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECitizenship%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3EMapping%20Citizenship%20in%20India%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710411845000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F29170506%2Fimage4.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fwho-belongs-and-how-locating-the-caa-in-todays-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20CAA%20represents%20a%20tendency%20in%20the%20ideological%20formulation%20of%20citizenship%20that%20redefines%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20political%20community.%20If%20the%20NRC%20as%20it%20has%20unfolded%20in%20Assam%20congealed%20the%20relationship%20between%20legal%20status%20and%20blood%20ties%2C%20the%20CAA%20has%20installed%20an%20exclusionary%20nationhood%20under%20the%20veneer%20of%20liberal%20citizenship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fwho-belongs-and-how-locating-the-caa-in-todays-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22All%20England%20Open%20Live%3A%20Sindhu%20On%20The%20Backfoot%2C%20Trails%20Se-Young%20In%201st%20Game%22%2C%22cont