y%20without%20work%2C%20and%20there%20is%20no%20work%20without%20the%20flow%20of%20energy.%20But%20we%20do%20not%20create%20energy.%20We%20can%20only%20take%20existing%20energy%20and%20change%20its%20form%2C%20converting%20heat%20energy%20into%20motion%20or%20motion%20into%20electricity%2C%20for%20instance.%20And%20as%20energy%20flows%20through%20the%20processes%20of%20doing%20work%2C%20converting%20from%20one%20form%20to%20another%2C%20some%20of%20it%20is%20lost%20at%20every%20step%2C%20irreversibly%20depleted%20as%20%3Cem%3Ewaste%20heat%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20recovered%20to%20perform%20work%2C%20including%20to%20support%20life.%20These%20rules%20governing%20energy%20flows%20of%20course%20also%20apply%20to%20the%20human%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20our%20presently%20dominant%20mythological%20universe%E2%80%94which%20guides%20policy%20today%20no%20less%20than%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-agricultural-revolution-an-alternate-telling%5C%22%3Eancient%20Sumerian%20belief%3C%2Fa%3E%20system%20guided%20theirs%E2%80%94doesn%E2%80%99t%20accept%20these%20kinds%20of%20empirical%20constraints.%20It%20teaches%20instead%20that%20different%20forms%20of%20energy%20and%20materials%20are%20perfectly%20substitutable%20and%20able%20to%20sustain%20energy%20use%20and%20economic%20growth%20without%20limits.%20Its%20stories%20dismiss%20the%20diminishment%20of%20the%20living%20world%20and%20dismemberment%20of%20its%20essential%20geochemical%20cycles%20as%20though%20they%E2%80%99re%20neutral%20to%20the%20flows%20of%20energy%20and%20materials%20that%20comprise%20the%20global%20economy.%20It%20even%20posits%20that%20technology%20can%20substantially%20%E2%80%98decouple%E2%80%99%20economic%20growth%20from%20consumption%20and%20its%20associated%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20411px)%2085vw%2C%20411px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22411%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896.jpg%20874w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-219x300.jpg%20219w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F11123728%2FIMG_2896-746x1024.jpg%20746w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696598%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22565%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20modern%20stories%20substitute%20money%20for%20energy%20and%20materials%2C%20and%20then%20reify%20money%20as%20a%20thing%20in%20itself.%20Disregarding%20physics%20and%20ecology%2C%20they%20foreground%20the%20finances%20that%20represent%20the%20flows%20of%20capital%20in%20the%20world.%20But%20the%20finances%20aren%E2%80%99t%20%3Cem%3Ereal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20that%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20account%20for%20the%20true%20biophysical%20cycles%20and%20interrelationships%20constraining%20the%20larger%20system%20which%20provides%20all%20that%20capital.%20Finances%20float%20above%20the%20world%2C%20when%20reality%20is%20enmeshed%20%3Cem%3Ewithin%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20world%3B%20they%20constitute%20merely%20a%20selectively%20descriptive%20artifice%2C%20an%20opaque%20bubble%20of%20reasoning%20that%20ultimately%20obstructs%20our%20view%20of%20what%E2%80%99s%20actually%20happening%20in%20the%20larger%2C%20biophysical%20world%20of%20which%20we%E2%80%99re%20an%20inseparable%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20modern%20story-verse%20lets%20us%20imagine%20that%20we%20can%20get%20more%20out%20of%20a%20system%20than%20what%20goes%20into%20it.%20We%20call%20this%20magic%20%3Cem%3Eprofit%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20it%20is%20a%20trick%20of%20accounting.%20For%20gains%20at%20the%20center%20of%20our%20finite%20system%20are%20actually%20losses%20from%20its%20peripheries%3B%20whatever%20we%20take%20as%20profit%20is%20ultimately%20felt%20as%20a%20loss%20to%20someone%20or%20something%20else.%20In%20the%20present%20world%2C%20that%20loss%20usually%20cuts%20most%20deeply%20into%20the%20non-human%20biosphere%20as%20well%20as%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20members%20of%20global%20society.%20Of%20course%2C%20our%20mythology%20simply%20labels%20losses%20to%20the%20biosphere%20or%20the%20exploitable%20classes%20as%20%3Cem%3Eexternalities%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20things%20that%20don%E2%80%99t%20concern%20us.%20Yet%20they%20do%20concern%20us%2C%20for%20by%20over-extracting%20from%20them%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20destroying%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fof-mice-and-men-energy-and-cancer%5C%22%3Ethe%20body%20within%20which%20we%20live%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20intervention%20that%20separates%20many%20of%20us%20from%20the%20toll%20our%20modern%20way%20of%20life%20extracts%20from%20the%20Earth-system%20is%20the%20windfall%20of%20combustible%20fossils%20we%E2%80%99ve%20found.%20These%20have%20temporarily%20expanded%20the%20pool%20of%20energy%20at%20our%20disposal%20by%20many%20thousand%20times%2C%20compared%20to%20when%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-human-animal-in-the-circle-of-life%5C%22%3Elived%20by%20the%20daily%20flows%20of%20solar%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20alone.%20This%20transient%20glut%20of%20energy%20has%20allowed%20us%20to%20build%20infrastructures%20and%20technologies%20that%20delay%20our%20awareness%20of%20some%20of%20the%20worst%20consequences%20of%20our%20overexploitation%E2%80%94or%20at%20least%20keep%20them%20hidden%20from%20the%20notice%20of%20the%20wealthier%20segments.%20Take%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20use%20of%20air-conditioning%20to%20fend%20off%20the%20rising%20heat%20of%20global%20warming.%20Or%20the%20daily%20transport%20of%20mountains%20of%20trash%20from%20urban%20centers%20to%20outlying%20areas%E2%80%94sometimes%20to%20other%20countries.%20Or%20fishing%20that%20uses%20industrial%20vessels%20to%20travel%20farther%2C%20faster%2C%20and%20longer%20and%20still%20bring%20back%20large%20hauls%20of%20seafood%2C%20even%20while%20ocean%20life%20rapidly%20collapses%3B%20meanwhile%2C%20many%20fisherfolk%20limited%20to%20paddle%20or%20wind%20power%20can%20no%20longer%20adequately%20feed%20themselves%20from%20near%20shore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThink%20of%20the%20use%20of%20artificial%20agro-chemicals%20that%20supplement%20our%20exhausted%2C%20depleted%20soils%2C%20enabling%20us%20to%20grow%20more%20food%20today%2C%20even%20while%20worsening%20soil%20depletion%20and%20water%20pollution%20in%20the%20longer%20term%E2%80%94not%20to%20mention%20the%20impact%20of%20such%20chemicals%20on%20human%20health.%20Consider%20the%20groundwater%20mechanically%20pumped%20for%20irrigation%20today%2C%20increasingly%20dehydrating%20those%20same%20lands%20into%20the%20future.%20Then%20there%E2%80%99s%20the%20fact%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fscience%2F2013%2Fnov%2F03%2Ffritz-haber-fertiliser-ammonia-centenary%2523%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%25252525201900%2525252520there%2525252520were%25252525201.6%2Cthe%2525252520food%2525252520nourished%2525252520by%2525252520them.%5C%22%3Eabout%20half%20the%20nitrogen%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20any%20human%20body%20(on%20average)%20now%20comes%20from%20fertilisers%20derived%20using%20natural%20gas%E2%80%94meaning%20at%20least%20half%20of%20us%20literally%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20even%20exist%20without%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20back%20of%20economic%20growth%2C%20especially%20the%20motorisation%20of%20transport%2C%20India%20today%20has%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fenergy%2Findia-be-largest-global-oil-demand-growth-driver-through-2030-iea-2024-02-07%2F%5C%22%3Eworld%E2%80%99s%20third%20highest%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20oil.%20On%20current%20trends%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20set%20to%20move%20into%20first%20position%20before%202030.%20As%20of%202021%E2%80%932022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cseindia.org%2Fthe-plastic-life-cycle-11509%5C%22%3Eover%2084%20per%20cent%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20this%20demand%20was%20met%20by%20imports%20of%20crude%20oil.%20But%20India%20aims%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ibef.org%2Findustry%2Foil-gas-india%5C%22%3Erapidly%20expand%20oil%20refining%20capacity%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20coming%20decades%2C%20increasing%20strategic%20reserves%20and%20meeting%20greater%20demand%2C%20not%20only%20for%20fuel%20but%20also%20for%20plastic%20and%20other%20petrochemical%20manufacturing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECombustible%20fossils%20have%20enabled%20us%20to%20separate%20our%20need%20for%20fire%20from%20the%20daily%20and%20seasonal%20cycles%20of%20solar%20replenishment%2C%20which%20had%20always%20limited%20how%20much%20work%20was%20possible%20before.%20Now%20we%20can%20make%20seemingly%20unlimited%20amounts%20of%20fire%E2%80%94extra-somatic%20energy%E2%80%94as%20fast%20as%20we%20want%2C%20deploying%20it%20to%20grow%20more%20food%2C%20increase%20the%20human%20population%2C%20and%20consume%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20resources%20at%20a%20rate%20%3Cem%3Eat%20least%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.overshootday.org%5C%22%3E1.7%20times%20the%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20takes%20to%20replenish%20what%20we%E2%80%99ve%20taken.%20Of%20course%2C%20this%20figure%20can%E2%80%99t%20account%20for%20resources%20that%20are%20non-renewable%20on%20any%20human%20timescale%2C%20like%20marble%20and%20copper%20and%20combustible%20fossils%2C%20so%20the%20true%20rate%20of%20over-consumption%20is%20actually%20far%20more%20extreme.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20clear%20enough%20that%20if%20we%E2%80%99re%20using%20excess%20energy%20to%20exploit%20any%20essential%20resources%20faster%20than%20the%20Earth-system%20can%20replenish%20them%2C%20then%20our%20rate%20of%20consumption%20is%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20%3Cem%3Eunsustainable.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%20a%20person%20who%20lives%20like%20a%20middle-income%20American%20uses%20extra-somatic%20energy%20greater%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenergyskeptic.com%2F2020%2Fenergy-slaves%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20labour%20of%20400%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20working%20on%20their%20behalf%20every%20day%E2%80%94you%20might%20say%20they%20have%20400%20%E2%80%98fossil-energy%20slaves.%E2%80%99%20Yet%20we%E2%80%99ve%20become%20so%20accustomed%20to%20this%20fossil%20energy%20that%20we%20take%20it%20as%20an%20entitlement%2C%20part%20of%20our%20casual%20expenditure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20glut%20of%20excess%20energy%20came%20as%20a%20boon%20to%20formerly%20enslaved%20humans%20and%20animals%20because%20humans%20and%20animals%20are%20more%20costly%20to%20maintain%20than%20dredging%20and%20delivering%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.apple.com%5C%22%3Eenergy%20from%20ancient%20sunlight%3C%2Fa%3E%20stored%20in%20combustible%20fossils.%20Systems%20of%20forced%20labor%20began%20to%20crumble%20away%20as%20the%20fossil%20energy%20juggernaut%20gained%20steam%20during%20the%2018th%20and%2019th%20centuries.%20Despite%20this%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20worth%20noting%20that%20there%20are%20more%20enslaved%20persons%20in%20the%20world%20today%20than%20at%20any%20previous%20time%20in%20history.%20Intimate%20and%20domestic%20work%2C%20commercial%20fishing%2C%20brick-making%2C%20and%20a%20few%20other%20contexts%20remain%2C%20in%20which%20fossil%20energy%20apparently%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20able%20to%20replace%20the%20scope%20of%20benefits%20derived%20from%20enslaved%20or%20exploited%20workers.%20This%20tracks%20with%20the%20logic%20of%20capitalism%2C%20whereby%20humans%20and%20other%20living%20things%20are%20commodified%20as%20labor%20or%20resource%20stocks%2C%20and%20the%20motive%20to%20profit%20off%20of%20them%20exerts%20downward%20pressure%20to%20exploit%20them%20as%20much%20as%20possible%2C%20literally%20stealing%20their%20life%20energy%20for%20the%20exploiter%E2%80%99s%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%98Fossil-energy%20slaves%E2%80%99%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20be%20fed%20and%20housed.%20But%20they%20do%20create%20an%20overload%20of%20excrement%20in%20the%20form%20of%20excess%20carbon%20dioxide%2C%20which%20heats%20the%20planet%20and%20acidifies%20the%20oceans%2C%20and%20sooty%20particulates%2C%20which%20soil%20the%20air.%20We%20have%20for%20centuries%20ignored%20these%20costs%2C%20while%20it%20has%20accrued%20to%20extremes%20that%20now%20threaten%20life%20as%20we%20know%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14123537%2FScreenshot-2024-03-14-at-12.35.07-PM.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14123537%2FScreenshot-2024-03-14-at-12.35.07-PM.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14123537%2FScreenshot-2024-03-14-at-12.35.07-PM-300x231.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14123537%2FScreenshot-2024-03-14-at-12.35.07-PM-1024x787.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-701576%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22922%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBy%20August%20of%202023%2C%20humans%20had%20already%20exceeded%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20to%20renew%20the%20resources%20we%20had%20used%2C%20globally%2C%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year.%20This%20means%20global%20human%20consumption%20requires%201.75%20Earths%20to%20meet%20its%20annual%20demand.%20Image%20source%3A%20Earth%20Overshoot%20Day.%20Image%20credit%3A%20National%20Footprint%20and%20Biocapacity%20Accounts%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20those%20who%20insist%20that%20technology%20can%20forever%20continue%20to%20shield%20us%20from%20the%20consequences%20of%20our%20actions%2C%20that%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20Invisible%20Hand%20of%20the%20market%20will%20guide%20us%20to%20solutions.%20But%20thus%20far%2C%20market-driven%20technological%20innovation%20has%20not%20proven%20itself%20to%20be%20a%20rectifying%20force%20in%20broadly%20addressing%20ecological%20balance.%20Rather%2C%20it%20manufactures%20human%20needs%2C%20which%20it%20then%20promises%20to%20fulfill%2C%20for%20good%20or%20ill%2C%20and%20without%20regard%20to%20equity%20or%20sustainability%20of%20any%20kind.%20No%20one%20has%20so%20far%20explained%20how%20a%20system%20set%20up%20to%20enrich%20small%20groups%20of%20investors%2C%20who%20will%20do%20whatever%20it%20takes%20to%20make%20their%20returns%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgrist.org%2Fbusiness-technology%2Fnone-of-the-worlds-top-industries-would-be-profitable-if-they-paid-for-the-natural-capital-they-use%2F%5C%22%3Eexternalizing%20the%20harms%20while%20privatizing%20the%20gains%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20might%20now%20begin%20to%20build%20a%20world%20in%20which%20environmental%20problems%20are%20solved%20without%20creating%20new%20ones%E2%80%94driving%20us%20deeper%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-agricultural-revolution-an-alternate-telling%5C%22%3Eour%20progress%20trap%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94or%20further%20exploiting%20people.%20Restoring%20ecological%20balance%20will%20never%20be%20the%20goal%20of%20this%20profit-maximising%20economic%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECapitalism%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dw2YEeeu-LKo%5C%22%3Eworks%20against%20cooperation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20mutual%20aid.%20It%20requires%20institutional%20poverty%20to%20keep%20labor%20cheap.%20Economic%20elites%20actually%20spoke%20this%20aloud%20in%20the%20US%20in%202021%2C%20when%20workers%20given%20economic%20relief%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20refused%20to%20return%20to%20work%20in%20some%20of%20the%20most%20exploited%20sectors%20of%20the%20economy.%20In%20response%2C%20elites%20unabashedly%20remarked%20that%20workers%20should%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20have%20been%20given%20financial%20assistance.%20Rather%2C%20they%20should%20have%20been%20kept%20economically%20desperate%20so%20as%20to%20induce%20them%20to%20continue%20working%20in%20poor%20conditions%20for%20low%20wages.%20As%20anthropological%20economist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmonthlyreview.org%2F2023%2F09%2F01%2Fthe-double-objective-of-democratic-ecosocialism%2F%5C%22%3EJason%20Hickel%20says%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%98It%20is%20critically%20important%20to%20understand%20that%20the%20dual%20social-ecological%20crisis%20is%20being%20driven%2C%20ultimately%2C%20by%20the%20capitalist%20system%20of%20production.%20The%20two%20dimensions%20are%20symptoms%20of%20the%20same%20underlying%20pathology.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cseindia.org%2Fthe-plastic-life-cycle-11509%5C%22%3Edemand%20for%20plastics%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20nearly%20tripled%20over%20the%20past%20twenty%20years.%20At%20best%2012%25%20of%20waste%20plastic%20ends%20up%20being%20recycled.%20Most%20of%20that%20is%20delivered%20by%20people%20who%20pick%20through%20waste%20heaps%20as%20a%20livelihood.%20Another%2020%25%20gets%20burned%2C%20sometimes%20in%20waste-to-energy%20facilities.%20Burning%20removes%20plastic%20from%20the%20environment%2C%20but%20produces%20toxic%20gasses%20and%20carbon%20emissions%20at%20a%20higher%20rate%20than%20coal.%20The%20remaining%2068%25%20of%20plastic%20waste%20remains%20as%20solid%20pollution%20in%20the%20environment%2C%20causing%20health%20issues%20for%20people%20and%20animals%2C%20terrestrial%20and%20marine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20promoting%20a%20belief%20that%20economies%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Four-insatiable-quest-for-fire%5C%22%3Egrow%20infinitely%20on%20a%20planet%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20finite%20materials%20and%20energy%20flows%2C%20modern%20mainstream%20economic%20models%20are%20completely%20untethered%20from%20biophysical%20realities.%20They%20amount%20to%20a%20dangerous%20delusion.%20And%20yet%2C%20they%20dominate%20the%20present%20conversation%20on%20how%20to%20maintain%20our%20only%20planetary%20home.%20We%20should%20be%20wary%20of%20advice%20promulgated%20by%20economists%20or%20scientists%E2%80%94or%20anyone%E2%80%94who%20makes%20claims%20in%20contradiction%20of%20biophysical%20constraints%20or%20who%20is%20disinclined%20to%20entertain%20a%20more%20holistic%20framing%20of%20our%20predicament%20and%20how%20our%20planetary%20system%20works%2C%20even%20acknowledging%20its%20many%20facets%20that%20remain%20still%20a%20mystery%20to%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20most%20orthodox%20neoliberal%20economists%2C%20such%20as%20William%20Nordhaus%2C%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nobelprize.org%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2Fnordhaus-lecture.pdf%5C%22%3Eprize-winning%3C%2Fa%3E%20economic%20analyses%20of%20the%20costs%20of%20global%20warming%20have%20become%20a%20standard%20approach%20for%20evaluating%20responses%20to%20climate%20change.%20Yet%20the%20conclusions%20seem%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmahb.stanford.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2FThe_appallingly_bad_neoclassical_economics_of_clim-1.pdf%5C%22%3Ebreathtakingly%20naive%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheintercept.com%2F2023%2F10%2F29%2Fwilliam-nordhaus-climate-economics%2F%5C%22%3Eregarding%20the%20effects%20this%20calamity%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20have%20on%20actual%20human%20bodies%20and%20endeavours%2C%20treating%20the%20problem%20as%20though%20the%20human%20system%20is%20separate%20from%20the%20Earth-system.%20One%20must%20recognize%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20mounting%20crop%20failures%20due%20to%20rising%20heat%20represent%20not%20merely%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2233864%5C%22%3Edrop%20in%20GDP%20contributed%20by%20a%20small%20sector%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20economy%20but%20famine%20and%20death%20for%20swathes%20of%20people%2C%20mass%20migration%2C%20social%20instability%2C%20geopolitical%20upheaval.%20I%20daresay%2C%20heat%20will%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20come%20to%20affect%20labor%20and%20productivity%20even%20among%20workers%20in%20air-conditioned%20offices%2C%20whom%20Nordhaus%20felt%20assured%20could%20simply%20continue%20business%20as%20usual.%20Analyses%20like%20these%20are%20a%20reminder%20that%20modes%20of%20denial%20come%20in%20many%20flavours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20myths%20of%20mainstream%20economics%20have%20infected%20multiple%20other%20disciplines%20too%2C%20colouring%20the%20way%20investigators%20frame%20their%20questions.%20They%E2%80%99re%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fclimate-scientists-concept-of-net-zero-is-a-dangerous-trap-157368%5C%22%3Ebuilt%20into%20the%20scientific%20analyses%20of%20the%20IPCC%3C%2Fa%3E%20reports%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20in%20promoting%20%E2%80%98net%20zero%E2%80%99%20as%20a%20sensible%20emissions%20reduction%20target.%20Yet%20%E2%80%98net%20zero%E2%80%99%20isn%E2%80%99t%20possible%20without%20massively%20scaled%20carbon%20capture%20infrastructures%E2%80%94which%20don%E2%80%99t%20exist!%20And%20while%20no%20evidence%20is%20forthcoming%20that%20they%20can%20%3Cem%3Eever%3C%2Fem%3E%20exist%2C%20%E2%80%98net%20zero%E2%80%99%20remains%20central%20to%20official%20conversations%20because%20it%20is%20the%20only%20%E2%80%98solution%E2%80%99%20that%20protects%20the%20economic%20growth%20imperative.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20most%20%E2%80%98hopeful%E2%80%99%20IPCC%20scenarios%20accept%20a%2067%20percent%20chance%20of%20restraining%20global%20warming%20to%20(maybe)%20sub-catastrophic%20levels%20(at%20least%20for%20the%20Global%20North%2C%20given%20it%E2%80%99s%20already%20passed%20the%20point%20of%20catastrophe%20for%20millions).%20Who%20would%20board%20a%20plane%20that%20had%20a%2033%20percent%20chance%20of%20crashing%3F%20Yet%20these%20are%20the%20approaches%20modelled%20and%20promoted%20by%20the%20IPCC%20because%20they%E2%80%99re%20the%20ones%20that%20can%20still%20be%20squared%20with%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20one%20of%20the%20mitigation%20pathways%20highlighted%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F1350178X.2022.2040740%3Fsrc%3Drecsys%5C%22%3EIPCC%20includes%20modelling%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20imagines%20growth%20curtailed%20through%20policy%20means%E2%80%94a%20managed%20reduction%20of%20%E2%80%98productivity%2C%E2%80%99%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unsw.edu.au%2Fnewsroom%2Fnews%2F2023%2F03%2Fdown-with-work---how-reducing-hours-in-the-workplace-could-help-%5C%22%3Eby%20reducing%20workdays%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20instance%E2%80%94or%20takes%20into%20account%20the%20possibility%20of%20economic%20collapse%20directly%20resulting%20from%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%20But%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20end-of-growth%20scenarios%20are%20the%20most%20likely%2C%20most%20necessary%2C%20and%20therefore%20most%20deserving%20of%20our%20attention.%20Equitably%20reducing%20and%20stabilising%20the%20size%20of%20humanity%E2%80%99s%20environmental%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fwildlife-biodiversity%2Fworld-overshoot-day-world-has-already-overshot-nature-s-budget-for-rest-of-the-year-84027%5C%22%3Efootprint%20on%20a%20global%20scale%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20only%20way%20to%20address%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-human-animal-in-the-circle-of-life%5C%22%3Eecological%20overshoot%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94which%20is%20the%20underlying%2C%20existential%20problem%20we%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20post-growth%20scenarios%20lie%20beyond%20the%20scope%20of%20establishmentarian%20discussion.%20Among%20the%20power%20brokers%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20simply%20taboo%20to%20question%20either%20the%20growth%20imperative%20or%20the%20superiority%20and%20absolute%20virtue%20of%20techno-industrial%20civilisation.%20It%E2%80%99s%20forbidden%20to%20question%20the%20business-as-usual%20material%20entitlements%20of%20the%20highest%20consuming%20sectors%20of%20global%20society%2C%20whatever%20the%20cost%20to%20the%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20self-delusional%20sleight-of-hand%20frequently%20employed%20is%20the%20promise%20that%20growing%20the%20economy%20will%20bring%20everyone%20along%20to%20some%20acceptable%20level%20of%20equity%20by%20promoting%20%E2%80%98development%E2%80%99%E2%80%94teasing%20the%20world%20with%20visions%20of%20everyone%20living%20like%20a%20comfortable%20American.%20But%20this%20is%20a%20fantasy%2C%20at%20best.%20Conjuring%20illusions%20of%20eternal%20growth%20is%20a%20way%20of%20stealing%20from%20the%20voiceless%E2%80%94including%20future%20generations%E2%80%94to%20enrich%20the%20most%20powerful%20in%20the%20present.%20Industrial%20%E2%80%98development%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20form%20of%20colonisation%2C%20in%20which%20Adivasis%20and%20Indigenous%20peoples%20are%20stripped%20of%20their%20autonomous%2C%20land-based%20livelihoods%2C%20and%20then%20reprogrammed%20into%20labourers%20and%20consumers%2C%20while%20their%20erstwhile%20resources%20are%20redeployed%20for%20industrial%20profits.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20modern%20economy%20is%20a%20Ponzi%20scheme.%20It%20delivers%20benefits%20to%20some%20today%20only%20by%20stealing%20vast%20resources%20from%20the%20most%20vulnerable%2C%20today%20and%20into%20the%20future.%20It%20is%20self-limiting.%20And%20it%20will%20implode.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20momentary%20surfeit%20of%20cheap%20and%20abundant%20excess%20energy%20for%20the%20past%20three%20or%20ten%20generations%20(depending%20upon%20one%E2%80%99s%20location)%20has%20made%20it%20possible%20to%20dangerously%20delude%20ourselves%20about%20how%20our%20planet%20actually%20works%2C%20to%20the%20point%20of%20constructing%20a%20story-verse%20utterly%20detached%20from%20the%20biophysical%20realities%20to%20which%20we%20nevertheless%20remain%20bound.%20Today%2C%20we%20of%20industrial%20civilisation%20belong%20to%20a%20death%20cult%20where%20the%20prasad%20offered%20by%20our%20high%20priests%20is%20oil.%20We%20gulp%20it%20down%2C%20believing%20it%20to%20be%20our%20salvation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%20that%20the%20proverbial%20pie%E2%80%94which%20is%20literally%20the%20material%20Earth%20and%20its%20sustainable%20energy%20flows%E2%80%94is%20fixed%20in%20size%3B%20it%20%3Cem%3Ecannot%3C%2Fem%3E%20be%20made%20larger.%20Attempts%20to%20enlarge%20it%20are%20foundationally%20destroying%20its%20ability%20to%20support%20multitudinous%20life%E2%80%94including%20humans%E2%80%94by%20causing%20global%20heating%2C%20extreme%20pollution%2C%20and%20biospheric%20collapse.%20Rather%20than%20fantasise%20about%20expanding%20it%2C%20we%20should%20be%20re-creating%20stories%20in%20resonance%20with%20what%20is%20biophysically%20true.%20We%20should%20be%20looking%20to%20redistribute%20what%20is%20real%2C%20equitably%2C%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20supports%20life%20across%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20biosphere.%20We%20should%20be%20trying%20to%20rediscover%20the%20holistic%20wisdom%20of%20non-industrial%20peoples%2C%20who%20understood%20themselves%20to%20be%20part%20of%20their%20environment%2C%20not%20separate%20from%20it%2C%20thereby%20rediscovering%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fmodern-myths-of-prehistory%5C%22%3Epotential%20human%20selves%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20beings%20who%20evolved%20to%20live%20in%20communities%20of%20shared%20meaning%20and%20mutual%20aid%2C%20not%20atomised%20nodes%20in%20de-socialised%20networks%2C%20locked%20into%20crass%20competition%20for%20basic%20subsistence%20or%20upward%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20us%2C%20though%2C%20are%20inextricably%20enmeshed%20within%20this%20hegemonic%20system%20of%20capitalist%20overexploitation%20and%20overconsumption.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20what%20can%20we%20hope%20for%3F%20Some%20thoughts%20on%20this%20in%20the%20next%20essay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EUsha%20Alexander%20trained%20in%20science%20and%20anthropology.%20After%20working%20for%20years%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20she%20now%20lives%20in%20Gurugram.%20She%E2%80%99s%20written%20two%20novels%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0The%20Legend%20of%20Virinara%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Only%20the%20Eyes%20Are%20Mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710402013000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14123037%2Feelco-bohtlingk-H9c9HuYfbbc-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Ffossil-fuels-and-modern-myths%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Today%2C%20we%20of%20industrial%20civilisation%20belong%20to%20a%20death%20cult%20where%20the%20prasad%20offered%20by%20our%20high%20priests%20is%20oil.%20We%20gulp%20it%20down%2C%20believing%20it%20to%20be%20our%20salvation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Ffossil-fuels-and-modern-myths%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Fremantle%20Owner%20RTL%E2%80%99s%20Revenues%2C%20Profits%20Take%20a%20Hit%20Due%20to%20Weak%20Advertising%20Market%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710401963000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FPoor-Things-003.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235941617%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Revenues%20at%20Bertelsmann%E2%80%99s%20Luxembourg-based%20RTL%20Group%2C%20a%20media%20giant%20which%20owns%20Fremantle%2C%20dipped%205.2%25%20to%20%E2%82%AC6.2%20billion%20(%246.7%20billion)%20for%20the%20financial%20year%202023.%20The%20company%20attributed%20this%20to%20lower%2